definition: plural marker for pronouns, and nouns referring to individuals

sentences.english: They climb walls, leap off buildings and spy on enemies.
sentences.chinese: 它們會爬牆，能跳下大樓，還能暗中監視敵人。

sentences.english: For instance, Christmas gifts and toys, they are exported around the world.
sentences.chinese: 例如，聖誕禮品和玩具，它們是出口世界各地。

sentences.english: They never allowed the government to develop trains.
sentences.chinese: 它們絕不允許政府開發鐵路。

sentences.english: So watch out for these tests because they happen all the time。
sentences.chinese: 所以，要當心這些測試，因爲它們無時不在。

sentences.english: These elements can be sorted, or processed in the order they appear.
sentences.chinese: 可以對這些元素排序，或以其出現的順序處理它們。

sentences.english: Their DNA was also loosening up and making memory genes more active.
sentences.chinese: 它們的DNA也鬆開了，使記憶體基因更加活躍。

sentences.english: The controls line up so that they can be read like an English sentence.
sentences.chinese: 控件整隊排列，使它們讀起來像一個英語句子。

sentences.english: They are incredibly sturdy, thanks to the durability of their bamboo hulls.
sentences.chinese: 它們非常堅固，感謝竹船的耐用。

sentences.english: So there's real possibility of one of them existing without the other.
sentences.chinese: 這麼一來它們就真得有可能獨立存在了。

sentences.english: These nonsense letter, they are only the night-blooming cereus blossom from the fingertip.
sentences.chinese: 這些胡言亂語的文字，它們只是指尖開出的曇花。

sentences.english: They can also be thought of as functions mapping classes to new subclasses.
sentences.chinese: 它們也可以被認爲是將類映射到新子類的函數。

sentences.english: Unlike most other fish, they are monogamous and mate for life.
sentences.chinese: 不像其他的魚類，它們是一夫一妻制並終生廝守。

sentences.english: Locals also lit Kongming lanterns, and sent them into the sky.
sentences.chinese: 當地人還點亮孔明燈，把它們放飛到天空中。

sentences.english: Don't let unexpressed emotions build up inside of you.
sentences.chinese: 若你有強烈的情感，挑出它們表達他們。

sentences.english: They are round and so they bring us good luck all the year round.
sentences.chinese: 它們都是圓的，能給我們帶來一年的好運氣。
